# CAOS_SEISMIC — example environment. Copy to `.env` (gitignored) and fill as needed.
# The REAL .env never enters git. Keep secrets in your own private secret manager.
# The catalog spine (USGS ComCat) needs NO credentials; most sources are open.

# ── Data access (mostly optional; open services need nothing) ──────────────
# USGS ComCat / FDSN: no key required.
# Restricted regional networks (e.g. JMA / NIED Hi-net) are registration-gated and
# INTERNAL-ONLY — never wire their credentials into this public repo.

# Optional override of the default FDSN base URL for the spine:
# COMCAT_FDSN_BASE=https://earthquake.usgs.gov/fdsnws/event/1/

# Polite contact string sent as a User-Agent to data services (recommended):
CAOS_SEISMIC_USER_AGENT=CAOS_SEISMIC/0.1 (+https://github.com/fsantibanezleal/CAOS_SEISMIC)

# ── git-as-data publishing (the daily job) ─────────────────────────────────
# The daily job commits ONLY results/ + manifests/ (scoped allowlist; never `git add -A`).
# The push credential is a dedicated least-privilege deploy key / fine-grained PAT scoped to
# THIS repo, stored in the local git credential store — NOT here, NOT committed.
# PUBLISH_BRANCH=main
# PUBLISH_REMOTE=origin
